Demo-addlcomments: I stopped answering questions because it is very time consuming (and I do not have a lot of time) and also because I disagree with some of the premises of the questions, eg, that there is a correct answer to questions that clearly could be answered in different ways depending on additional contextual information that is not available in the survey. For examples, it does not make much sense to ask for the "right" number of communities in a small network with only a handful of nodes. Also, it was very difficult for me to see network visualization with large numbers of nodes, and to try to estimate numbers of nodes and edges, especially in visualizations (like circles) that are not designed for this task: many edges cannot be seen. I found this survey frustrating. Sorry.

Demo-addlcomments: I stopped answering questions because it is very time consuming (and I do not have a lot of time) and also because I disagree with some of the premises of the questions, eg, that there is a correct answer to questions that clearly could be answered in different ways depending on additional contextual information that is not available in the survey. For examples, it does not make much sense to ask for the "right" number of communities in a small network with only a handful of nodes. Also, it was very difficult for me to see network visualization with large numbers of nodes, and to try to estimate numbers of nodes and edges, especially in visualizations (like circles) that are not designed for this task: many edges cannot be seen. I found this survey frustrating. Sorry.
